.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-1-12::.
City: hamburg, prague, new-york, liverpool, paris, colone
The people use 6 different means of transport: bike, bus, jet-ski, motorbike, scooter, van
1. the person driving the bus is on the far left##1
2. the person traveling to liverpool is on the left of the person traveling to prague##1
3. the person driving the scooter is on the right of the person traveling to paris##1
4. the person driving the motorbike is the person traveling to liverpool##1
5. the person driving the van is on the left of the person driving the jet-ski##1
6. the person traveling to colone is on the left of the person traveling to liverpool##1
7. the person traveling to new-york is on the left of the person driving the bike##1
8. the person driving the bus is on the left of the person traveling to colone##1
9. the person driving the van is on the left of the person traveling to new-york##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |    2    |     3     |   4   |    5    |    6    |
| City   | paris | colone | liverpool    | prague | new-york  | hamburg |
| Transport     | bus    | scooter | motorbike | van   | jet-ski | bike    |

